UID:TW4fSkolEW90wQvLORQnZ
SUMMARY:Bikes & Bats
DTSTAMP:20260619T133039Z
DTSTART:20260620T190000Z
DESCRIPTION:Join Buffalo Bayou Partnership and BikeHouston for a batty good
	 time with a bike ride to the Waugh Bridge Bat Colony! \nBring your bike f
	or an evening ride along Buffalo Bayou to the Waugh Drive Bridge\, where y
	ou’ll witness an unforgettable sight—more than 300\,000 Mexican free-taile
	d bats emerging at sunset. Along the way\, bat expert DeAndra Ramsey will 
	share insights about these fascinating and important creatures—affectionat
	ely known as “sky puppies.” Spots are limited\, so reserve yours today! \n
	Cost\n$10 \nDuration\n2 hours / 3 miles \nMeeting Location\nThe Water Work
	s in Buffalo Bayou Park (105-B Sabine St) \nTICKETS\n\nhttps://buffalobayo
	u.org/event/2026-bikes-and-bats-2/\n\nFrom Buffalo Bayou Partnership
URL:https://buffalobayou.org/event/2026-bikes-and-bats-2/
LOCATION:THE WATER WORKS\, 105 Sabine Street\, Houston\, TX\, 77007\, Unite
	d States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:buffalo-bayou-partnership
CATEGORIES:Buffalo Bayou Partnership
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
IMAGE;VALUE=URI;DISPLAY=BADGE;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://buffalobayou.org/w
 p-content/uploads/2023/04/boat.jpg
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://buffalobayou.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/
 04/boat.jpg
UID:5i5FsAdRwOZtTuOeG41yL
SUMMARY:Buffalo Bayou Cruise: Bats
DTSTAMP:20260619T133039Z
DTSTART:20260620T192000Z
DESCRIPTION:Sail the scenic waterway on a 90-minute\, guided tour from down
	town to Waugh Drive Bridge and back to watch the emergence of the 250\,000
	+ Mexican free-tailed bats that live under the bridge. \nOur knowledgeable
	 guide will share details about the bats’ eating patterns\, behavior and c
	ontributions to the bayou’s ecosystem. Space is limited\, and boat tours f
	ill up fast. Boat departs 45 minutes before sunset. \nCost\nStarting at $3
	0/person \nDuration\n90 minutes \nDeparture location\n Allen’s Landing (10
	19 Commerce St.) \nPlease note\, children must be at least four years old 
	to board the pontoon boat. \n  \nPURCHASE TICKETS\n\nhttps://buffalobayou.
	org/event/2026-june-buffalo-bayou-cruise-bats-30-3/\n\nFrom Buffalo Bayou 
	Partnership
URL:https://buffalobayou.org/event/2026-june-buffalo-bayou-cruise-bats-30-3
	/
LOCATION:ALLEN’S LANDING\, 1001 Commerce Street\, Houston\, TX\, 77002\, Un
	ited States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:buffalo-bayou-partnership
CATEGORIES:Buffalo Bayou Partnership
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
